\begin_layout Section
Session Information Frame
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Session Information Frame 
\emph default
manages the sessions running on a HadesFIX instance.
 A HadesFIX session can be in a couple of different states described as
 follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
ACTIVE - Session is logged in and exchanges messages in sync
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
INACTIVE - Session is not logged in to the counter-party but is created
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
DISCONNECTED - The transport layer has been disconnected manually
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
FROZEN - Session is logged in to the counter-party but is in a state that
 only responds to Heartbeat and TestRequest messages received from the counter-p
arty.
 All the other messages are rejected.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
SHUTDOWN - The session is not running (not in the memory anymore)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The contextual menu is displayed when right click on a session (see below).
 The contextual menu options are enabled/disabled based on the session status.
 The session contextual menu options are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Refresh - Updates the current session Status and receive/transmit sequence
 numbers.
 This option is available in all the session states.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Transport Disconnect - Disconnects the transport layer.
 This will work different on the Sell compare with Buy engine session type.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
For a Sell session the TCP server worker will be shutdown but the session
 state will be preserved.
 When the Buy side reconnects it will continue the normal flow of messages
 assuming it has kept its session state
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For a Buy session the TCP client will be shutdown.
 The client can reconnect automatically if configured to do so or may be
 reconnected manually.
 In both cases the session state is preserved.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Transport Connect - Attempts to manually connect a disconnected transport.
 The option is only available in DISCONNECTED state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Sequence Reset - Sends a SequenceReset message to the counter-party.
 Prior the Rx sequence number must be set to a sequence number greater than
 the current sequence.
 If the request is successful the remote session Tx sequence number is synchroni
ze to the value of the local set Rx sequence number.
 The option is available only in ACTIVE state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Session Reset - Sends a Login reset message that resets both Rx and Tx sequence
 numbers to 1.
 The option is available only in ACTIVE state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Froze - Sets the current session in FROZEN state.
 All the messages other then Heartbeat and TestRequest are rejected by a
 Reject message sent back to the Counter-party.
 The option is available only in ACTIVE state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Thaw - Unset the FROZEN state of the session and resume the normal message
 flow.
 The option is available only in FROZEN state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stop - Kills the selected session and destroys all the data structures of
 this session.
 The option is available only in ACTIVE state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Start - Starts a session that has been killed manually or died unexpectedly.
 The option is available only in SHUTDOWN state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Session Stats - Populates the 
\emph on
Session Statistics 
\emph default
frame with session data since the session has been started.
\end_layout

