\begin_layout Description
sesfrz <session_id> - “freezes” a session.
 A frozen session responds only to Heartbeat and TestRequest messages and
 reject all the other messages.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sesthw <session_id> - “thaws” a session already frozen.
 Activates the session and relay/responds to all the messages received.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
seskil <session_id> - disconnect the session and distroys the memory structures.
 The session can be restarted using the sesrun command.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sesrun <session_id> - creates the session data structures and attempts to
 connect the session transport for the Client side.
 For the Server side the session is ready to accept incoming connections.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sesdis <session_id> - disconnects session’s transport.
 A client session can be reconnected using the sescon command.
 For the Server side the session is ready to accept incoming connections.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sescon <session_id> - connects session’s transport.
 A client session will attempt to reconnect as per configuration.
 The Server side does not use this command.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sesrst <session_id> - resets the Rx and Tx sequence numbers to 1 by sending
 a Logon message with ResetSeqNumFlag field set to true.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sessta <session_id> - retrieve statistics data for the transport, session
 and streams.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
seqrst <session_id> 
\series bold
<new_seq_num>
\series default
 - sends a SequenceReset message in Reset mode (the GapFillFlag set to N)
 in order to reestablish a session after a unrecoverable error.
 The new_seq_num parameter needs to be greater than the current Rx sequence
 number and will become the current Rx sequence number.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
srvdwn shutsdown the HadesFIX instance gracefully allowing for the messages
 buffered to be transmitted/relayed.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
srvkil abruptly shutsdown the HadesFIX instance.
 All the messages that were not transmitted/relayed will be lost.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sessrx <session_id> 
\series bold
<new_seq_num>
\series default
 - this command should be only used for debugging the protocol.
 It sets directly the Rx sequence number in the Protocol layer.
 The session needs to be “frozen” before using the command.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
sesstx <session_id> 
\series bold
<new_seq_num>
\series default
 - this command should be only useed for debugging the protocol.
 It sets directly the Tx sequenece number in the Protocol layer.
 The session needs to be “frozen” before using the command.
 
